The paper discusses a routing algorithm for the Lightning Network, which is a decentralized payment network built on top of the Bitcoin blockchain. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also addresses issues related to security and cryptography (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY) in the context of the Lightning Network.
